### DB Explorer API Tests
### Sprint 1 & 2: Backend Foundation + AI Layer

### Variables
@baseUrl = https://localhost:7189
@token = YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
@connectionId = YOUR_CONNECTION_ID_HERE

###
# Step 1: Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "Admin@123"
}

### Save token from response above

###
# Step 2: Get connections list
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/connections
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Save connectionId from response

###
# Step 3: Get cache status
# Check if analysis data is available
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/db-explorer/{{connectionId}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected response:
# {
#   "hasData": true,
#   "schemaAvailable": true,
#   "analysisAvailable": true,
#   "graphAvailable": true,
#   "scannedAt": "2024-03-19T...",
#   "tableCount": 18,
#   "issueCount": 2
# }

###
# Step 4: Analyze database (trigger full crawl + AI analysis)
# This will:
# - Scan schema with statistics
# - Run AI analysis (domain classification, table roles, health check)
# - Build graph data
# - Cache everything
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/db-explorer/{{connectionId}}/analyze
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected response:
# {
#   "message": "Analysis complete",
#   "tables": 18,
#   "issues": 2,
#   "domain": "E-commerce Platform",
#   "cached": false
# }

###
# Step 4: Get database overview (summary card data)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/db-explorer/{{connectionId}}/overview
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected response:
# {
#   "domain": "E-commerce Platform",
#   "summary": "System for managing...",
#   "tableCount": 18,
#   "columnCount": 156,
#   "totalRows": 2300000,
#   "modules": [
#     {
#       "name": "Product Catalog",
#       "description": "...",
#       "tables": ["Products", "Categories"]
#     }
#   ],
#   "issueCount": 2,
#   "scannedAt": "2024-03-19T...",
#   "confidence": 0.95
# }

