###
# Step 12: Invalidate cache (force refresh)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/db-explorer/{{connectionId}}/cache
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected response:
# {
#   "message": "Cache invalidated successfully"
# }

###
# Step 13: Re-analyze with force refresh
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/db-explorer/{{connectionId}}/analyze?forceRefresh=true
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected response:
# {
#   "message": "Analysis complete",
#   "tables": 18,
#   "issues": 2,
#   "domain": "E-commerce Platform",
#   "cached": false
# }

## 🎯 Testing Checklist

### ✅ Phase 1 - Schema Crawler
- [ ] POST /analyze - Crawls schema successfully
- [ ] GET /tables - Returns all tables with row counts
- [ ] GET /tables/{name} - Returns table detail with columns, indexes
- [ ] Statistics collected (row count, null rate, distinct count)

### ✅ Phase 2 - AI Analyzer
- [ ] Domain classification works (E-commerce, CRM, etc.)
- [ ] Table roles assigned correctly (Master, Transaction, Bridge, etc.)
- [ ] Modules identified and grouped
- [ ] Health issues detected (missing indexes, orphan tables, etc.)

### ✅ Phase 3 - Graph Builder
- [ ] GET /graph - Returns nodes and edges
- [ ] Nodes have correct role colors
- [ ] Edges show relationships correctly
- [ ] Relationship types detected (one-to-many, many-to-many)

### ✅ Phase 4 - Caching
- [ ] First call triggers analysis
- [ ] Second call uses cache (fast response)
- [ ] DELETE /cache invalidates successfully
- [ ] forceRefresh=true bypasses cache

## 📝 Notes

### Performance
- First analysis: 5-10 seconds (depends on DB size)
- Cached responses: <100ms
- Statistics collection: Optional, can be disabled for large tables

### AI Analysis
- Uses LLM to classify domain and assign roles
- Fallback to heuristics if LLM fails
- Confidence score indicates reliability

### Cache Strategy
- Schema: 1 hour TTL
- Analysis: 24 hours TTL
- Graph: 24 hours TTL
- Auto-invalidation on schema change (fingerprint check)
